HEADWORD: Hermeneutics
<hw>Her`me*neu"tics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ (sc.
<?/).]</ety> <def>The science of interpretation and explanation;
exegesis; esp., that branch of theology which defines the laws whereby
the meaning of the Scriptures is to be ascertained.</def>
